<taxonomicName authority="Ahrens, Fabrizi &amp; Liu" authorityName="Ahrens, Fabrizi &amp; Liu" authorityYear="2021" box="[328,830,1771,1797]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Maladera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="199" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lushuiensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[328,570,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="199" pageNumber="200">Maladera lushuiensis</emphasis>
Ahrens, Fabrizi &amp; Liu
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[840,900,1772,1798]" pageId="199" pageNumber="200" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from the other species of the group with the dorsomedian sinuation of phallobase covered by a wide and large dorsal process by having the latter deeply emarginate medially and the parameres having no basal lobe.
</paragraph>
